SIMPLE: equiponderate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equiponderate
<hw>E`qui*pon"der*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Equi-</ets> + L. <ets>ponderare</ets> to weigh. See
<er>Ponderate</er>.]</ety> <def>To be equal in weight; to weigh as much
as another thing.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Wilkins.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equiponderate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Equiponderate
<hw>E`qui*pon"der*ate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make equal in
weight; to counterbalance.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧More than
<xex>equiponderated</xex> the declension in that direction.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>De Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equiponderous</ent>⟦br⟧
